# EAS Build archive ignore — MUST live at the git repository root.
#
# EAS copies the archive starting from the git root (this dir), NOT from the
# app subdirectory. Without this file, `eas build` from apps/nuru uploads the
# ENTIRE monorepo (all apps + .git = ~80 MB) instead of the ~1.7 MB nuru app.
#
# Nuru is a standalone Expo app (excluded from workspaces, no @mcloud/* deps),
# so we ignore everything and re-include only apps/nuru. Any OTHER EAS app in
# this repo would need its own include line added here.

# Ignore everything by default...
/*
apps/*

# ...then re-include only the nuru app.
!apps
!apps/nuru
!apps/nuru/**

# Even within nuru, never upload heavy/generated dirs.
apps/nuru/node_modules
apps/nuru/dist
apps/nuru/web-build
apps/nuru/.expo
apps/nuru/.expo-shared
apps/nuru/android
apps/nuru/ios
apps/nuru/.kotlin
apps/nuru/*.aab
apps/nuru/*.apk
